Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.47,0:00:08.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间  空间和物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to an endless, expanding existence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始不断膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of time,space and matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.68,0:00:15.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天  我们都在解密这神秘莫测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking the mysterious,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.07,0:00:17.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,令人疯狂的极端之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mind-blowing, the deadly secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.47,0:00:20.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a place we call the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.05,0:00:25.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星人在哪里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where are the Martians?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:34.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在毒气笼罩的红色星球表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the red planet's, poison-packed surface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.55,0:00:37.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抑或是新发现的水源中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or in newly found sources of water?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.95,0:00:42.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星生命从致命大碰撞中生存下来了吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Did Martian life survive an apocalyptic attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.31,0:00:49.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是微生物  还是大怪物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are Martians like microbial or monstrous?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:52.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终答案即将揭晓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at last, the answers are here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.32,0:00:56.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在《火星新证据》\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In Mars: the new evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.74,0:01:11.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\pos(90,26)}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}肯尼迪航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.50,0:01:13.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\pos(90,26)}{\fn微软雅黑\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}2010年4月15日
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.89,0:01:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我相信我们能将人类送入火星轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I believe we can send humans to orbit Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并让他们安全返航\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and return them safely to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.25,0:01:19.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,紧接着实现在火星登陆的计划\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a landing on Mars will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.40,0:01:25.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们降落在火星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we land on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.41,0:01:31.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许会看到成千上万的火星人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there may be billions of Martians waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.82,0:01:40.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们的长相可能不是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only they probably won't t look like this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.65,0:01:42.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也不是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or this,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.10,0:01:52.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,微生物  细菌进化到在此星球上生存生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Microbes, bacteria evolved to survive on a planet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.25,0:01:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的大气压力只有地球的1%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with 1% of Earth's atmospheric pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:02:00.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是个温度能从220摄氏度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an arid world where temperatures can plunge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.14,0:02:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,骤降至零下的干旱之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to 220 degrees below zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.66,0:02:07.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管表层环境看起来如此恶劣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, even if that upper-surface is so nasty,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但并不意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that doesn't t mean
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.60,0:02:10.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掩藏在下面的境况也如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that just a little ways under the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.04,0:02:14.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}布鲁斯·贝茨\N美国行星协会
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.43,0:02:15.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是火星上微生物的极乐天堂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wouldn't be a much happier place for microbial life on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.79,0:02:20.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星上有生命存在吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is there life on Mars?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.18,0:02:23.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}吉姆·贝尔\N康奈尔大学
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.03,0:02:23.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十年前  我的答案和现在迥然不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just a decade ago, my answer would have been very different than it is today
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.70,0:02:25.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为这些年获取了大量信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we've learnt so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.45,0:02:28.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few decades ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:30.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这看起来像是科幻剧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would have seemed like science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.47,0:02:33.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而现在我们知道  在地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we now know that on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:38.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些微生物聚集在海底的热泉周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some bacteria cluster around thermal vents at the bottom of the sea;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.89,0:02:43.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些生长在南极地区冰层下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}others thrive in pockets of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.08,0:02:45.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,12英尺中的少量液态水里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inside 12 feet of antarctic ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:52.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}阿什温·瓦萨瓦达\N美国宇航局/喷射推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.87,0:02:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们对于地球微生物的了解已经很深入了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our knowledge of microbial life on Earth has increased so much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.98,0:02:52.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时我想  某些原始微生物是不是可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that, I think, you know, there's still a good chance that some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.41,0:02:59.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在火星形成并存在的呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}primitive life may have formed on Mars and existed there at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.19,0:03:04.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命是如何在火星上形成的呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could life have first formed on Mars?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:07.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是由于一个闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe with a flash of lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.69,0:03:10.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2006年的春天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spring of 2006.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:13.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管当时一些科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even as some scientists are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:15.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,声称火星上没有闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}claiming Mars doesn't t have lightning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.09,0:03:18.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的微波探测器发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth-based microwave detectors find it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.40,0:03:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星上有充满静电的红色尘暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in friction-filled storms of red dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.67,0:03:27.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹利\N格里菲斯天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.94,0:03:25.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这并不是我们所熟知的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's not lightning like we know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.28,0:03:26.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雨前的闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}associated with rainstorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星上没有雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, it doesn't rain on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.09,0:03:30.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称之为干闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's what's called dry lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.67,0:03:34.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种干闪电  或者说静电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this dry lightning, or static electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能就是火星生命起源的契机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could have been the trigger for Martian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.70,0:03:43.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦闪电  就能够产生一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once you have lightning, you've got a new source of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:48.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变大气中化学成分的新能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can affect your chemistry and alter things in the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.01,0:03:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一定程度上来说  即使表面也是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even on the surface, at some level.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.49,0:03:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个著名的实验试图复制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A famous experiment seeking to replicate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:56.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球生命的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the creation of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:04:00.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在水和普通气体的混合物中通上电流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ran an electric current through a mix of water and common gases,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.05,0:04:01.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生一种溶液\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating a soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:04.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包含有机化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}containing organic compounds
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.37,0:04:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和生命基本组成物  氨基酸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the building blocks of life: amino acids.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.18,0:04:11.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过电流刺激\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By hitting things, with electrical discharges,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.24,0:04:12.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然不能创造生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could not necessarily generate life,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也许可以营造生命起源的先决条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but maybe make the preconditions for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,干闪电确是火星生命起源的助推器吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But did dry lightning,, help jumpstart life on Mars?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.47,0:04:25.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是彻底破坏任何生存可能的杀手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or did it kill the chance for any life at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:30.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星上的闪电能创造过氧化氢等物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lightning on Mars could create things like hydrogen peroxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:33.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些物质将生成其他化学成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which could then lead to other chemicals that would
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:36.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,摧毁火星表面的一切有机物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}destroy organic material and sterilize the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.97,0:04:41.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是生之希望  还是死之深渊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life-giving jumper cable or fatal electric chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.93,0:04:44.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们仍然不清楚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The jury is still out on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.49,0:04:47.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尘暴闪电对火星有什么影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what dust storm lightning has done to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.86,0:04:51.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们总是刚以为已经了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, what always happens with Mars is about the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.26,0:04:52.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we think we understand it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.83,0:04:55.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又会有新的发现  让我们意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we discover new things that make us realize
